{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781996727,"nonce":"jiS87GHvaskFtWySxdigMmRqcQk=","title":"Add upsert: PostgreSQL `INSERT … ON CONFLICT …` and MySQL","message":"`INSERT … ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE …`.\n\nHighest-value write feature; very common. Also the most dialect-divergent piece,\nso it needs careful `Dialect` seams.\n\n- Builder: extend the insert builder —\n  `.on_conflict((cols)).do_nothing()` and\n  `.on_conflict((cols)).do_update(|excluded| (col.set(excluded.col), …))`.\n  The closure receives an \"excluded/new row\" handle for the SET expressions.\n- Dialect divergence (the crux):\n  - PG: `ON CONFLICT (target) DO UPDATE SET … | DO NOTHING`, references\n    `EXCLUDED.col`.\n  - MySQL: `ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE …`, references `VALUES(col)` / `new.col`,\n    NO explicit conflict target, NO `DO NOTHING` (emulate via `INSERT IGNORE` or\n    `col = col`).\n  Add `Dialect` methods for the conflict clause + the excluded-row reference.\n- Type-level: reuse `UpdateAssignments` for the SET list; conflict-target columns\n  are a column-key tuple (v1: accept a column list; later validate it's a declared\n  UNIQUE/PK set).\n- Render: append the conflict clause in `write_insert_with_params` (render.rs);\n  thread SET params after the inserted-row params.\n\ncrates/squealy/src/query.rs + squealy-macros (write builder), render.rs +\nsquealy-test/src/sql.rs, the `Dialect` trait + both backend dialects, lib.rs,\n+ tests.\n\nRender for PG `DO UPDATE`/`DO NOTHING` and MySQL `ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE`,\nEXCLUDED vs VALUES() reference, bind ordering, compile-fail, `#[ignore]`\nround-trips on both backends.\n\nMedium-large (~one busy session) — dialect divergence + excluded-row handle.\n\nPG-first, then MySQL emulation of the same builder surface.","files":null}]}